HEADWORD: Universality
<hw>U`ni*ver*sal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Universalties</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>universalit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of
being universal; unlimited extension or application; generality; --
distinguished from <xex>particularity</xex>; <as>as, the
<ex>unversality</ex> of a proposition; the <ex>unversality</ex> of sin;
the <ex>unversality</ex> of the Deluge.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Universalize</ent>⟦br⟧
